  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7099.5 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-4.2B) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5.0B), dealers are likely buying the dip aggressively after the recent wall break event. The PIN regime with 48.9B total GEX suggests strong mean-reversion forces, with dealers expected to continue buying any weakness toward 7100 and selling strength into the 7150-7200 zone where positive gamma exceeds +5.9B. Key levels to watch: 7100 defense (dealers buy), 7115 resistance flip, and 7150-7200 supply zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect a bounce back toward 7150 as dealers buy this dip near major support.",
